  "verdict": "COVERAGE-AT-ENGAGE DOES NOT SEPARATE. (1) The warmup routed-mass curve is near task-invariant at the 50-tok engage window: cov@23 = 79% (range 73-82%) for html AND all 11 coding prompts, Kmin-cov90 ~= 38 for every task -- so a coverage rule picks ~the same K regardless of task and is not a task-width discriminator. (2) Two normalisations differ ~4x: warmup 1-cov@23 = 0.21 (def-1, routed/selected-6) vs live S1 = 0.81 (def-2, full-256); the trace logs only the 6 selected experts so def-2 is UNOBSERVABLE offline -- the identity S1_pred=1-cov is false. (3) Neither normalisation orders outcomes: survivor K91 S1=0.845 < collapser K23-rotate S1=0.811 (non-monotone); and keep-23 STATIC survives (L3) while keep-23 ROTATE collapses at the identical warmup coverage 0.79. The separators are actuation mode (static>>rotate), mask provenance (session>>cold), and token budget -- none in the coverage curve. USE the curve only to avoid UNDER-provisioning: cov90-sizing raises the fatal fixed K23 to ~38 uniformly (untested; needs a pod A/B)."
